parameters: Oh, elder brother! You've returned safely!

Lord Fuma, you seem to be in good health, which is a relief.
I returned yesterday.

Ha ha! No need to be so formal. I've sent everyone away. You
can speak as you usually do, elder brother.

This mission was indeed exhausting. I'm not as young as I
used to be. This morning, I even overslept.

You've worked hard. What's the situation in the capital? Are
they really planning to advance to Kanto?

Indeed. The number of soldiers, guns, and warships was
extraordinary. It's likely that by the end of the year, they
will mobilize the entire army and march to Odawara.
How many troops does the enemy have? About 50,000?

----!! 200,000 troops...!? Can the capital's army really
organize such a massive force?

If the armies from Oshu join them, the total force could
reach 250,000. I've already reported this to Odawara before
returning to the village. Osaka Castle has ample provisions,
and the rice stores are well stocked. They'll have no
problem leading a large army to Kanto.

...Hey, Kotaro. There's something I can only discuss with
you, my true brother. Will you listen?
...? Something you can only discuss with me...?

This is just between us, but should we not join the
capital's army? I am convinced that is how our Fuma clan
will survive.

Yes. If things continue as they are, they will seriously
attack us. Any lord who does not submit will be made an
example of for all the daimyo across the country. There will
be no compromise.

And depending on the outcome of this great war, our Fuma
clan could be swept away by the tides of history.

I swear to the gods above and below that I am not lying. We
haven't been fed false information by the enemy. The
opponent is an extraordinary daimyo who nearly has the whole
country in his grasp. I want to avoid the destruction of our
village. Understand me, Kotaro--

...Rebellion is impossible. We participated in the recent
battle in Kozuke that violated the peace edict. How could we
possibly turn traitor now? The capital would never allow it.

We Fuma have served the Odawara side for five generations.
We've received ample rewards and gold from them. That's why
we were able to change from thatched to tiled roofing on the
mansion while elder brother was spying in the capital.

...Foolish. Tiled roofs are nothing unusual in Kyoto or
Osaka. Temples, shrines, and castles there naturally have
them. Even merchants and common houses are tiled.

~~~~~! Are you insulting me?! Even if you are my true
brother, I will not tolerate such disrespect as the head of
the Fuma!

"A year in the countryside is like an afternoon nap in
Kyoto." Anyway, they are overwhelmingly superior to us in
every way. It pains me to admit it...

Excuse me for interrupting your conversation. We were
thinking of holding a celebration tonight for Uncle
Chutaro's safe return. Is that alright?

Momiji! We're having an important discussion here! Don't
just open the sliding doors without being called!

Sorry! It wasn't Momiji's idea; it was mine! Please forgive
us, boss--!

...Understood. Anyway, you've done well on your mission.
Let's hold a banquet tonight to celebrate Chutaro's return.
Inform everyone in the Fuma village, Aomaru.

Heheh! Thanks a lot! I'll let everyone know! We'll prepare
loads of food!
I apologize for interrupting your important conversation...

Tch! The boss didn't have to get so angry. Don't you think
so, Momiji?

(...? Father and Chutaro-san both had grim expressions. I
wonder if something happened...)
...It seems you are deep in thought, my lord--

Houzukijii... You were secretly listening to our
conversation from behind the scenes, weren't you?
I apologize. It's just a habit of a ninja...

What do you honestly think... about the proposal from my
brother to align with the upper ranks?

Ho ho ho. It's impossible for an old man like me to judge.
Isn't it a gamble either way?

To seek profit by defecting to the upper ranks and
preserving the Fuma village, or to honor our debts and
continue assisting the Odawara side as we have always
done... I leave all decisions to you, Lord Kotaro, the head
of the Fuma clan. We, your party, will simply become blades
to cut down our enemies if you so command--

(He seems to be sleeping peacefully. I wonder what kind of
dreams he's having.)
Welcome back. How was your meeting with Lord Kotaro?

Ah. Perhaps I spoke too harshly. But... the future of Fuma
is at stake. I had to speak my mind no matter what.

While you were away, rumors reached the village as well.
People are saying that it might truly lead to war... Is the
upper ranks' army really that strong and numerous?

Hmm. If we make the wrong decision, this village might
eventually be engulfed in flames. It's a troubling situation
indeed...

...I see... I just hope that children like Karin, who know
nothing of this, will be spared from any disaster...

Oh, have you woken up? When the day turns to dusk, Kotaro is
going to host a banquet. Would you like to come with Karin?

I understand. I've been feeling well lately, so I will bring
Karin along.

--Has everyone gathered? Then let us commence tonight's
feast to celebrate Chutaro's safe return from his long
espionage mission. It's an open house tonight. Have fun
everyone.

You've worked hard on your mission, Lord Chutaro. Come,
let's drink.

This village is lively and nice. It's been five years since
I came to the Fuma village, and I'm very grateful that they
accepted a ronin like me whose lord's house had fallen.

Aibara-dono is from Echizen, if I recall correctly. Not just
anyone is accepted into the Fuma. It's because you are a
master of martial arts and also an expert blacksmith.

Heh, it may sound self-serving, but skills do save one's
life. For someone like me who became a ronin and wandered
after my lord's house fell, this Fuma village has been my
savior. If there's a battle, I'll be the first to spearhead
the charge.
...Well, I do hope that no major battles occur.

By the way, Aibara-dono, could you show me the sword you
carry? I've been curious about it ever since I heard rumors
that it was made over 600 years ago...

I'm sorry, Aibara-san... That sword is not to be shown
lightly as it's strictly forbidden to be taken outside the
gate, and my grandmother has strictly told me not to show it
to others...

Hmm, is that so... No, I wanted to see this divine-named
treasure sword to improve my blacksmithing skills... But if
it's forbidden, then there's nothing to be done. I apologize
for asking too much.

Oh, that reminds me. The sword you made for me on my long
journey has become loose at the hilt and guard. Could you
fix it?

Hmm. Then I shall take it with me. I'll repair it and bring
it back after tomorrow.
My apologies. I'm counting on you.

Come now, Chutaro-sama\I[15], don't just talk with Aibara-
dono, please enjoy my sake as well

Yes, my apologies, Iekiku-- but if you pour so much sake
into every cup, it will be troublesome, won't it?

Ufufufu\I[15], Chutaro-sama can handle his liquor, can't he?
Come now, don't be shy and please drink up\I[15]

----!? (This sake... upon closer inspection, it has a
strange color...)

Whoa there, Chutaro-san. You better not drink that sake. Sis
has mixed in some love potion and aphrodisiacs into that
dangerous drink. Who knows what will happen if you drink it
Hey! Aomaru! Don't say unnecessary things--!
...May I dispose of this sake in the garden?

I've tested it many times to perfect it! I made it with
great care! Even just one sip would be fine, please drink
it!

...Excuse me, Iekiku-san, could you please not give my
husband such suspicious drinks?

Ugege--!? Ko-, Korin-san!? Even your daughter Karin-chan--?
Well, this is rare? It's unusual for you to show up at a
banquet? Ahahaha!

Karin has become more settled now. If she cries, I'll take
her outside... We won't disturb the banquet.

Is that so? Then Chutaro-san, please try my special sake
another time? Ufufu--\I[15]

Hm...? What's with that look? As a ninja, there's no way I
would drink such suspicious sake.

Hey!-- Aomaru! If you hadn't said anything, Chutaro-sama
would have been mine! (Gripping tightly!)

Ouch ouch ouch! Sis, give it a rest already! Chutaro-san and
Korin-san have been married for years now! They even have a
baby!
...Huh? That's unusual. You brought Karin-chan along too.

Yes. It's important to get her used to being around lots of
people so she doesn't become shy.

Ah, but she looks very sleepy. It can't be helped. Babies
need their sleep after all.

The party is in full swing, but it can't be helped. If we
let her sleep here, she might catch a cold. It might be time
to head back.
What's this, brother? Are you leaving already?
I'm sorry. It seems Karin is already sleepy.

Karin, who carries the blood of my brother and Lady Korin,
has a promising future. She's over 10 years younger than
Momiji, but as cousins, I hope they get along well and build
a bright future for the Fuma clan.
Indeed... As a parent, all I can wish for is her happiness.

While Chutaro-san was away, Kotaro-san provided us with a
lot of support. We even received many radishes.
Is that so? I apologize for the trouble, Kotaro.

It's only natural. This mission was of great importance. I
sent my most skilled ninja, my brother, to the capital on my
orders. Momiji has also done well in reducing the burden of
child-rearing on Lady Korin during these three months.
Hehe... I'm glad to hear you say that, Father.

Brother, before you leave, let's have a toast--wishing for
the continued prosperity of our Fuma village.

Ah, I am grateful, Lord--here's to the success and
prosperity of our Fuma party--

Nothing particularly changed over the course of three
months. If I had to say, it would be that the prices of
weapons and armor have risen in Odawara.

I heard you returned yesterday. It must have been tough
being on an intelligence mission for three months.

Oh, Nakataro-dono! Welcome back. The boss has been waiting
for you.

I heard you returned home yesterday. I'm glad to hear you're
safe and sound.

Um... since yesterday, the master's behavior has been
unusual... I wonder if something happened?

This is for you, Nakataro-dono. The lord is waiting at the
[Demon Shrine]. He wishes to speak with you alone, so please
come quickly.
...He wants me to come to the Demon Shrine? Understood.

This is a message for Nakataro-dono. The lord is waiting for
you at the [Oni Shrine]. He wishes to speak with you alone,
so please come quickly.
